<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <%- include('head') %>
  <title><%= locals.title %></title>
  <meta name="description" content="<%= locals.description %>" />
  <meta property="og:title" content="<%= locals.title %>" />
  <meta property="og:description" content="<%= locals.description %>" />
  <meta property="og:url" content="https://oldschoolgames.eu/how-to-play" />
  <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
  <meta property="og:site_name" content="OldSchoolGames" />
  <meta property="og:image" content="https://oldschoolgames.eu/images/navbar.webp" />
</head>

<body class="layout">
  <%- include('navbar') %> <%- include('left-sidebar') %>
  <main>
    <div class="container">
      <%- include('flash') %>
      <section>
        <h1 class="text-lg" style="margin-bottom: 20px">
          How to Play MS-DOS Games
        </h1>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 25px">
          MS-DOS games from the 80s and 90s were built for a very different era of computing.
          If you're new to retro gaming, some things can feel a little unfamiliar at first.
          This guide covers the essentials — controls, saving your progress, and tips for getting the best experience in your browser.
        </p>

        <!-- Quick start -->
        <div style="margin-bottom: 30px; padding: 15px 20px; background: rgba(var(--primary-rgb), 0.08); border: 1px solid rgba(var(--primary-rgb), 0.3); border-radius: var(--border-radius);">
          <h2 class="text-md" style="margin: 0 0 10px; color: rgb(var(--primary-rgb))">Quick Start</h2>
          <ol style="padding-left: 20px; line-height: 2; margin: 0">
            <li>Open any game and wait for the emulator to load (usually a few seconds).</li>
            <li>Click inside the game window to give it keyboard/mouse focus.</li>
            <li>Press <kbd>Alt + Enter</kbd> to switch to fullscreen for the best experience.</li>
            <li>Read the game's intro screen — many games display controls right at the start.</li>
            <li>If the game asks for a key press to continue, just press any key.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <!-- Browser keyboard shortcuts -->
        <h2 class="text-md" style="margin-bottom: 10px">Browser &amp; Emulator Shortcuts</h2>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 10px">
          These shortcuts work in the browser while the game window is focused:
        </p>
        <div style="overflow-x: auto; margin-bottom: 25px">
          <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em">
            <thead>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(var(--border-rgb)); color: rgb(var(--accent-rgb))">
                <th style="text-align: left; padding: 8px 12px">Shortcut</th>
                <th style="text-align: left; padding: 8px 12px">What it does</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(var(--border-rgb), 0.4)">
                <td style="padding: 8px 12px"><kbd>Alt + Enter</kbd></td>
                <td style="padding: 8px 12px">Toggle fullscreen mode</td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(var(--border-rgb), 0.4)">
                <td style="padding: 8px 12px"><kbd>Ctrl + F10</kbd></td>
                <td style="padding: 8px 12px">Release / capture mouse cursor</td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(var(--border-rgb), 0.4)">
                <td style="padding: 8px 12px"><kbd>Ctrl + F5</kbd></td>
                <td style="padding: 8px 12px">Take a screenshot (DOSBox)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td style="padding: 8px 12px"><kbd>Esc</kbd></td>
                <td style="padding: 8px 12px">Often pauses or exits menus in games</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <!-- Saving games -->
        <h2 class="text-md" style="margin-bottom: 10px">Saving Your Progress</h2>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 10px">
          Saving in MS-DOS games is very different from game to game — there was no universal standard. Here are the most common methods:
        </p>
        <ul style="padding-left: 20px; line-height: 2; margin-bottom: 10px">
          <li>
            <strong>In-game save menu</strong> — Most RPGs and adventure games have a dedicated
            <em>Save Game</em> option in their in-game menu, usually accessed via <kbd>Esc</kbd> or <kbd>F1</kbd>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Save slots</strong> — Many action and strategy games let you press a key like <kbd>F5</kbd>
            (save) and <kbd>F7</kbd> or <kbd>F8</kbd> (load). Always check the game's help or README.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Passwords</strong> — Some older games (especially platformers and action games from the late 80s)
            don't save at all — instead they give you a password at the end of each level to resume later.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>No saving</strong> — Arcade-style games typically have no save feature. You play until you run
            out of lives, just like in an arcade.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Auto-save</strong> — Some games save automatically when you exit or at certain checkpoints.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 25px">
          <strong>Tip:</strong> If you're unsure how to save, check whether the game has a manual linked on its page — many DOS games came with detailed printed manuals.
        </p>

        <!-- Common controls -->
        <h2 class="text-md" style="margin-bottom: 10px">Common Controls by Genre</h2>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 10px">
          Controls varied a lot between genres. Here's a general overview:
        </p>

        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(270px, 1fr)); gap: 15px; margin-bottom: 25px">
          <div style="padding: 15px; background: rgba(var(--border-rgb), 0.2); border: 1px solid rgb(var(--border-rgb)); border-radius: var(--border-radius)">
            <strong style="color: rgb(var(--accent-rgb))">Action / Platformers</strong>
            <ul style="padding-left: 18px; margin: 8px 0 0; line-height: 1.8">
              <li>Arrow keys — move / jump</li>
              <li><kbd>Alt</kbd> or <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> — fire / attack</li>
              <li><kbd>Space</kbd> — jump (in some games)</li>
              <li>Joystick / gamepad supported in many titles</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div style="padding: 15px; background: rgba(var(--border-rgb), 0.2); border: 1px solid rgb(var(--border-rgb)); border-radius: var(--border-radius)">
            <strong style="color: rgb(var(--accent-rgb))">Adventure / RPG</strong>
            <ul style="padding-left: 18px; margin: 8px 0 0; line-height: 1.8">
              <li>Mouse — click to interact / move</li>
              <li>Arrow keys — navigate menus or move character</li>
              <li><kbd>Enter</kbd> — confirm / talk</li>
              <li><kbd>Esc</kbd> — back / menu</li>
              <li><kbd>F1</kbd> — help / save in many games</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div style="padding: 15px; background: rgba(var(--border-rgb), 0.2); border: 1px solid rgb(var(--border-rgb)); border-radius: var(--border-radius)">
            <strong style="color: rgb(var(--accent-rgb))">First-Person Shooters</strong>
            <ul style="padding-left: 18px; margin: 8px 0 0; line-height: 1.8">
              <li>Arrow keys — move &amp; turn</li>
              <li><kbd>Ctrl</kbd> — shoot</li>
              <li><kbd>Space</kbd> — open doors / interact</li>
              <li><kbd>Alt</kbd> + arrows — strafe</li>
              <li>Number keys — switch weapons</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div style="padding: 15px; background: rgba(var(--border-rgb), 0.2); border: 1px solid rgb(var(--border-rgb)); border-radius: var(--border-radius)">
            <strong style="color: rgb(var(--accent-rgb))">Strategy / Simulation</strong>
            <ul style="padding-left: 18px; margin: 8px 0 0; line-height: 1.8">
              <li>Mouse — select and give orders</li>
              <li>Arrow keys or <kbd>WASD</kbd> — scroll the map</li>
              <li><kbd>Space</kbd> or <kbd>P</kbd> — pause</li>
              <li>Number keys — speeds or unit groups</li>
              <li><kbd>F10</kbd> — main menu in many games</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div style="padding: 15px; background: rgba(var(--border-rgb), 0.2); border: 1px solid rgb(var(--border-rgb)); border-radius: var(--border-radius)">
            <strong style="color: rgb(var(--accent-rgb))">Sports &amp; Racing</strong>
            <ul style="padding-left: 18px; margin: 8px 0 0; line-height: 1.8">
              <li>Arrow keys — steer / move</li>
              <li><kbd>Space</kbd> — accelerate / action</li>
              <li><kbd>Ctrl</kbd> / <kbd>Alt</kbd> — brake / special</li>
              <li>Joystick often works better than keyboard</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div style="padding: 15px; background: rgba(var(--border-rgb), 0.2); border: 1px solid rgb(var(--border-rgb)); border-radius: var(--border-radius)">
            <strong style="color: rgb(var(--accent-rgb))">Puzzle / Arcade</strong>
            <ul style="padding-left: 18px; margin: 8px 0 0; line-height: 1.8">
              <li>Arrow keys — move / navigate</li>
              <li><kbd>Space</kbd> or <kbd>Enter</kbd> — confirm / action</li>
              <li><kbd>Esc</kbd> — pause or quit</li>
              <li>Often very simple — controls shown on title screen</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Mouse capture -->
        <h2 class="text-md" style="margin-bottom: 10px">Mouse in Games</h2>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 25px">
          Some games (like first-person shooters or strategy games) capture your mouse cursor so it stays inside the game window.
          To release the cursor — for example to switch tabs or resize the window — press
          <kbd>Ctrl + F10</kbd>. To recapture it, click inside the game again.
        </p>

        <!-- Sound -->
        <h2 class="text-md" style="margin-bottom: 10px">Sound &amp; Music</h2>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 10px">
          Many DOS games were written for specific sound hardware (AdLib, Sound Blaster, PC speaker).
          The emulator tries to match the best sound card automatically, but in some games you may need to configure
          sound in the in-game setup or at the main menu. Look for an option like <em>Sound Setup</em>, <em>Options</em>,
          or a separate <code>SETUP.EXE</code> / <code>SETSOUND.EXE</code> in the game's start menu.
        </p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 25px">
          If a game starts in silence, check the volume settings in your browser and on your system — some games
          default to very low volume.
        </p>

        <!-- General tips -->
        <h2 class="text-md" style="margin-bottom: 10px">General Tips</h2>
        <ul style="padding-left: 20px; line-height: 2; margin-bottom: 25px">
          <li>
            <strong>Read the intro screens</strong> — most DOS games display basic controls or instructions
            when you first start them. Don't skip them too fast.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Check the manual</strong> — if a game has a manual linked on its page, it's worth a look.
            Many DOS games were complex and relied on the manual to explain mechanics that aren't obvious in-game.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Use fullscreen</strong> — press <kbd>Alt + Enter</kbd> for a more immersive experience.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Be patient with load times</strong> — some larger games take a few extra seconds to boot up in the emulator.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Game won't start?</strong> — try clicking directly on the game window and pressing any key. Some games wait for user input before starting.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Controls not working?</strong> — make sure the game window has focus (click inside it). Your browser may be intercepting some key combinations.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Every game is different</strong> — the controls above are general guidelines. When in doubt,
            look at the game's help screen (<kbd>F1</kbd> or <kbd>?</kbd> key in most games) or the manual.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p style="color: rgb(var(--muted-rgb)); font-size: 0.9em">
          Have a question or found something that's not covered here?
          Feel free to leave a comment on any game page and the community can help.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
  <%- include('right-sidebar') %>
  <%- include('footer') %>
</body>

</html>
